=head1 DESCRIPTION

The Lustre metadata performance configuration of an Amazon FSx for
Lustre file system using a C<PERSISTENT_2> deployment type. The
configuration enables the file system to support increasing metadata
performance.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Iops => Int

The number of Metadata IOPS provisioned for the file system. Valid
values are C<1500>, C<3000>, C<6000>, C<12000>, and multiples of
C<12000> up to a maximum of C<192000>.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Mode => Str

The metadata configuration mode for provisioning Metadata IOPS for the
file system.

=over

=item *

In AUTOMATIC mode, FSx for Lustre automatically provisions and scales
the number of Metadata IOPS on your file system based on your file
system storage capacity.

=item *

In USER_PROVISIONED mode, you can choose to specify the number of
Metadata IOPS to provision for your file system.

=back




